    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting a MemoryError when i try to run this script that processes a huge csv file using pandas. i think it's because i'm loading everything into a list at once. what's the actual difference between using a list comprehension vs a generator function when it comes to memory usage? i need to fix this before the deployment tomorrow.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The main difference is how they produce values: a list comprehension builds and stores *all* results in memory simultaneously. In contrast, a generator function uses `yield` to create an iterator that produces values one at a time, on demand. This \"lazy evaluation\" means only one item exists in memory at any given time, making generators vastly superior for handling huge datasets like your CSV. Use generators or chunking with pandas instead of loading everything into a list.",
      "source": "target",
