      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the error was purely due to creating a massive list, switching to a generator will resolve the memory spike. To diagnose a potential leak, monitor your system's peak memory usage over time while the script runs and then inspect the Python process object in a debugger. Look for objects that are continuously accumulating or references that are not being properly released after their intended use. If memory usage steadily climbs without plateauing, you likely have a true memory leak.",
